<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="I" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Impatience" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Impatience,</orth> 1) want of composure in pain and suffering: <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.3.51" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 3, 51</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.3.42" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C III, 3, 42</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 4.15.79" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. IV, 15, 79</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.4.112" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 4, 112</bibl>.<lb />2) eagerness of desire: <cit><quote>i. chokes her pleading tongue,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 217" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 217</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>all patience and i.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 5.2.103" default="NO" valid="yes">As V, 2, 103</bibl></cit>.
<lb />3) anger, passion, rage: <cit><quote>my heart is ready to crack with i.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.2.301" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. II, 2, 301</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>sheathe thy i.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.3.88" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 3, 88</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>how i. loureth in your face,</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 2.1.86" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. II, 1, 86</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. jn 4.3.32" default="NO" valid="yes">John IV, 3, 32</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.7.8" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A IV, 7, 8</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 2.2.38" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 2, 38</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.156" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 156</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 5.6.146" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. V, 6, 146</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 1.3.61" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. I, 3, 61</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 2.1.248" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 248</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.6.5" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 6, 5</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 2.2.68" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 2, 68</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 2.6.43" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 6, 43</bibl>.
